a. Require the Accounting Unit to check the Report of Collection and Deposits (RCDs) against the official receipts and deposit slips as source documents to ensure correctness of recorded income/revenue collected and the amount deposited, pursuant to Section 35 (e), of the NGAS Manual Volume I.

Require the Municipal Accountant to furnish the COA a copy of the Abstract of General Collections and the Real Property Tax Collections of the Municipality monthly;

Require the Municipal Treasurer to submit the Consolidated Report of Accountability for Accountable Forms (RAAFs) and the Abstract of Collections to the COA for the months under our audit period and for the ensuing months pursuant to Section 51 of the NGAS Manual Volume II.

Initiate the conduct of a complete physical inventory of the Municipality’s properties  by creating an Inventory Committee composed of a representative each from the Mayor’s Office, from the General Services Office (or the Municipal Treasurer’s Office) and a representative from each department to prepare the necessary procedures in the proper and orderly conduct of the physical count of the all the property, plant and equipment and inventories owned by the Municipality;
Require the Inventory Committee  to conduct the physical count of all the properties recorded in the books and those not yet recorded but actually found in the LGU offices/premises and to prepare the corresponding inventory reports thereof; and reconcile them with the accounting records to come up with the correct account balances in the financial statement.
Require the Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant to maintain stock, property and ledger cards, respectively to properly account the receipt and disposition of property and supplies.  The Office of the Municipal Treasurer should request additional staff for the conduct of the physical inventory.

